    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (74.75) and **Junior Caminero** (72.66). **Yordan Alvarez** remains our premier start, boasting an elite xwOBA of .393 and a favorable matchup against Warren, while **Junior Caminero** benefits significantly from an 11% SP skill boost and a high-leverage #2 spot in the order. **Trea Turner** (67.15) and **Caleb Durbin** (69.42) round out our top-tier plays; **Caleb Durbin** is particularly compelling today, as his projection spiked due to a massive 16% park factor enhancement and a weak opposing arm, making him a high-ceiling utility start despite his lower slot in the batting order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s card involved keeping **Carson Benge** (48.62) on the bench. While his projection profile is solid, he fell short of the threshold required to displace players like **Pete Crow-Armstrong** or **Josh Smith**, whose dynamic platoon advantages and projected stolen base opportunities\u2014critical in our 5x5 Roto context\u2014pushed them ahead in efficiency. Regarding risk, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** carries the most uncertainty; as his lineup status is currently pending, his score is predicated on an assumed #9 spot. Should that move, or should Sheehan\u2019s efficiency exceed his 3.20 xERA, we may see the Zebras\u2019 bottom-third production dip. Additionally, while **Dillon Dingler** (61.15) provides strong value, his performance is tethered to the 100% stolen base potential against the opposing battery, a situational nuance we will be monitoring closely throughout the game.",
